<item>
            <title>[JCR-714] TCK: Test root path not escaped when used in XPath queries</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-714</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>A repository implementation might use a test root path that contains names that need _xXXXX_ escaping when used in XPath queries. Currently the TCK just uses the test path as-is when constructing queries. Even though this only affects few repositories (I&amp;#39;ve heard of one legacy connector to run into this problem), it would be good to add the proper escaping.</description>
